# Phase B ŌĆö Route-Decision Trace

> Goal: every request routed through `auto/*`, `combo:*`, or a custom strategy leaves a navigable forensic trail that explains *why* each candidate was considered, why the cascade chose what it chose, and where the chain fell through.

---

## 1. Why now

Self-healing and the autoCombo scoring engine are opaque from the outside ŌĆö failures look like "we picked B and that timed out" with no record of why A was *not* picked. The user's pain point: requests failing too often inside harnesses, no way to see the decision chain, no way to investigate cost/speed optimisations from real data. Once traces exist, every downstream thing (cost derivation, anomaly detection, SLM evaluator) plugs in trivially.

## 2. What the trace must capture

Per request, write one row into `route_traces` and one or more rows into `route_trace_steps`:

| Field | Type | Source | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `request_id` | TEXT PK | existing request correlation id | Same id also appears in `call_logs` for cross-link |
| `session_id` | TEXT | If session-keyed (`auto/smart`, `auto/coding`) | Enables rollup on session boundaries |
| `ts` | TEXT (ISO) | `Date.now()` | UTC |
| `route_kind` | TEXT CHECK in (`auto`, `combo`, `manual`, `recovery`) | `combo.resolve()` caller | |
| `strategy` | TEXT | `RouterStrategy.name` (`rules`, `cost`, `latency`, `sla-aware`, `lkgp`, `learning`, custom) | |
| `model_requested` | TEXT | input `model` field | |
| `model_chosen` | TEXT | `RoutingDecision.model` | |
| `provider_chosen` | TEXT | `RoutingDecision.provider` | |
| `final_score` | REAL | `RoutingDecision.finalScore` | |
| `candidates_json` | TEXT | ordered snapshot of every candidate score | JSON-encoded array |
| `cascade_json` | TEXT | per-step explainer | JSON-encoded array of `{step, reason, candidate}` |
| `latency_ms_total` | INTEGER | request lifecycle span | |
| `cascade_steps` | INTEGER | number of retry attempts | `0` if first-choice won |
| `outcome` | TEXT CHECK in (`success`, `fallback`, `error`) | terminal state | |
| `error_class` | TEXT NULL | classifier output (`PROVIDER_ERROR_TYPES.*`) | only on `error` |
| `error_kind` | TEXT NULL | structured `{kind, retryable, retryAfterMs}` | only on `error` |
| `observed_input_tokens` | INTEGER NULL | call completion | |
| `observed_output_tokens` | INTEGER NULL | call completion | |
| `observed_cache_write_tokens` | INTEGER NULL | call completion (Anthropic) | |
| `observed_cache_read_tokens` | INTEGER NULL | call completion | |
| `learned_failure_rate` | REAL NULL | future Phase B step | 0..1 |
| `anomaly_signal` | TEXT NULL | future Phase B step | z-score string or null |
| `user_agent` | TEXT NULL | upstream request UA | |

Indexes: `(ts DESC)`, `(session_id, ts)`, `(model_requested, ts)`, `(outcome, error_class, ts)`, plus FTS5 on `cascade_json` (SQLite already supported via `db/migrations` patterns ŌĆö verify before adding).

## 3. Where the recorder hooks

Three touchpoints are enough to capture everything that matters:

1. **`traceRecorder.startRequest(reqCtx)`** at the top of `combo.resolve()` (or whichever function currently invokes the strategy). Returns a `TraceHandle`.
2. **`traceRecorder.recordStep(handle, candidate, score, reason)`** is called from inside `scorePool()` (`open-sse/services/autoCombo/scoring.ts`) for *every candidate*, and again for each retry/cycle inside `accountFallback` ŌĆö only the score/decision values, never the LLM payload.
3. **`traceRecorder.finish(handle, decision, outcome, error?)`** after the executor returns ŌĆö writes the row and the steps.

Boundary discipline per `AGENTS.md`: do not modify `routerStrategy.ts` or `scoring.ts` *implementation* ŌĆö instead read their output. The recorder is a new file (`open-sse/services/routing/traceRecorder.ts`) that subscribes to decisions emitted by the strategy. To make that work, `scorePool` needs to wrap its result with a `scorePoolWithAudit()` shim; that shim is opt-in via `OMNIROUTE_TRACE=1`. Off by default ŌĆö zero overhead path through.

## 4. Persistence

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS route_traces (
  request_id                  TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  session_id                  TEXT,
  ts                          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),
  route_kind                  TEXT NOT NULL,
  strategy                    TEXT NOT NULL,
  model_requested             TEXT NOT NULL,
  model_chosen                TEXT,
  provider_chosen             TEXT,
  final_score                 REAL,
  candidates_json             TEXT,
  cascade_json                TEXT,
  latency_ms_total            INTEGER,
  cascade_steps               INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  outcome                     TEXT NOT NULL,
  error_class                 TEXT,
  error_kind                  TEXT,
  observed_input_tokens       INTEGER,
  observed_output_tokens      INTEGER,
  observed_cache_write_tokens INTEGER,
  observed_cache_read_tokens  INTEGER,
  learned_failure_rate        REAL,
  anomaly_signal              TEXT,
  user_agent                  TEXT
);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_route_traces_ts        ON route_traces (ts DESC);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_route_traces_session   ON route_traces (session_id, ts);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_route_traces_model     ON route_traces (model_requested, ts);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_route_traces_outcome   ON route_traces (outcome, error_class, ts);
```

Migration number: `113_route_traces.sql` (Phase A will use `112_provider_health_history.sql` for the z-score backing table ŌĆö see Phase A spec, to be written).

## 5. Read API

`src/app/api/v1/traces/route.ts` ŌĆö list endpoint, paginated by ts DESC; filters: `request_id`, `session_id`, `model`, `provider`, `strategy`, `outcome`, `error_class`, `from_ts`, `to_ts`.
`src/app/api/v1/traces/[id]/route.ts` ŌĆö single trace, returns full `candidates_json` / `cascade_json` decoded.

Both follow the existing pattern in `src/app/api/v1/` (Zod-validated, auth-gated per `AGENTS.md:208-220`).

## 6. Dashboard

`src/app/(dashboard)/dashboard/traces/[requestId]/page.tsx` ŌĆö server component. Renders:

- Header: `requested`, `chosen`, `strategy`, `final_score`, `latency_ms_total`, `outcome`.
- *Compare table*: one row per candidate, columns `provider`, `model`, `score`, `composite reasons`. Sortable.
- *Cascade timeline*: vertical timeline of `{step, reason, candidate, transition}` so the user sees exactly why model A ŌåÆ B ŌåÆ C.
- *Side panel*: tokens, cache tokens, error class (if any), anomaly signal (when Phase A online).
- A *session roll-up* view at `/dashboard/traces/session/[sessionId]` that aggregates per-session waste / progression once Phase C ships.

## 7. Tests

- `tests/unit/trace-recorder.test.ts` ŌĆö start/record/finish lifecycle; verifies on/off flag handling; verifies failure isolation (a thrown recorder does not break routing).
- `tests/integration/traces-cascade-rewrite.test.ts` ŌĆö synthesises a cascade with two fallbacks; asserts `cascade_json` decodes to the expected shape and `cascade_steps` matches.
- `tests/e2e/route-trace.spec.ts` ŌĆö Playwright run via existing `tests/e2e/*.spec.ts` style. Drives `POST /v1/chat/completions` with `model: "auto/coding"` against a mock server that fails once then succeeds; asserts a complete `route_traces` row + navigable dashboard URL.

## 8. Risks & mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Trace size balloons SQLite | `candidates_json` capped at top N=20; cascade capped at N=10 steps; truncate older than 30d via existing `cleanup.ts` pattern. |
| Recorder overhead when off | Off-by-default via `OMNIROUTE_TRACE=1`; recorder functions early-return if disabled. |
| User request payload leakage | Recorder only stores metadata, never message body. Audit at PR time. |
| Migration conflicts | Use `113` (upstream may add between drafts ŌĆö re-check before commit). |

## 9. Open questions

1. Body text / metadata about the *prompt* shape ŌĆö should we include a SHA-256 of the prompt so the user can correlate traces without storing PII? *Recommended: yes, hashes only.*
2. Cache the trace JSON columns or normalise cascade steps into their own table? *Recommended: JSON columns for v1; normalise later if cadence demands.*
3. `error_kind` schema ŌĆö should it be the standard `PROVIDER_ERROR_TYPES` enum or a richer `{kind, retryable, retryAfterMs, rawStatus}` object? *Recommended: richer object.*
